tests: assert is_palindrome('a man a plan a canal panama') == False
assert sort_numbers('three one five') == 'one three five'
assert sort_numbers('nine eight seven six') == 'six seven eight nine'
assert sort_numbers('zero two four six eight') == 'zero two four six eight'
assert sort_numbers('four four four') == 'four four four'
assert sort_numbers('one three two') == 'one two three'
assert is_palindrome('A man a plan a canal Panama').lower().replace(" ", "") == True
assert is_palindrome('no lemon, no melon').lower().replace(" ", "").replace(",", "") == True
assert anti_shuffle('a b c') == 'a b c'
assert anti_shuffle('The quick brown fox') == 'The cikqu bnoorw fox'
assert anti_shuffle('jumps over the lazy dog') == 'jmpsu eo rv the adl yzog'
assert is_bored("The sky is blue. The sun is shining. I love this weather") == 1
assert is_bored("I am bored. I am tired. I want to go home.") == 3
assert is_bored("I'm not really bored, just tired. But I guess I am a bit bored too.") == 0
assert is_bored("I think, therefore I am. Am I bored? Yes!") == 2
assert is_bored("Is it just me, or is it getting boring here? I think it is.") == 1
assert is_bored("I? Really? I! Indeed. I.") == 4
assert encode('This is a message') == 'tHKS KS C MGSSCGG'
assert words_string("Hi, my name is John") == ["Hi", "my", "name", "is", "John"]
assert words_string("One, two, three, four, five, six") == ["One", "two", "three", "four", "five", "six"]
assert histogram('a b c a b') == {'a': 2, 'b': 2}
assert histogram('b b b b a') == {'b': 4}
assert histogram('d d d d d') == {'d': 5}
assert histogram('a a a b b c') == {'a': 3, 'b': 2}
assert histogram('x y z x y z x') == {'x': 3, 'y': 2, 'z': 2}

assert odd_count(['', '0024', '567']) == ["the number of odd elements 0n the str0ng 0 of the 0nput.", "the number of odd elements 0n the str0ng 0 of the 0nput.", "the number of odd elements 3n the str3ng 3 of the 3nput."]
assert select_words("Mary had a little lamb", 4) == ["little"]
assert select_words("Mary had a little lamb", 3) == ["Mary", "lamb"]
assert select_words("a e i o u", 1) == []
assert select_words("b c d f g", 1) == ["b", "c", "d", "f", "g"]
assert split_words("Hello world! How are you?") == ["Hello", "world!", "How", "are", "you?"]
assert words_in_sentence("lets go for swimming") == "go for"
assert words_in_sentence("prime numbers are special") == "prime are"
assert words_in_sentence("one two three four five six seven eight nine ten") == "two three five seven"
assert words_in_sentence("I love to code") == "I to"
assert words_in_sentence("We are testing different lengths") == "We are testing lengths"
